claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A flowchart depicting the study cohort selection: initial cohort (N=18,467), applied exclusion criteria to yield an analyzable cohort (N=14,590), then split into Controls (N=12,837) and Influenza cases (N=1,803), each further subdivided by vaccination status (RIV4, SD-IIV4, Unvaccinated) with respective counts. does not support the claim because the figure only presents participant flow and vaccine group counts without any information on antigenic matching to WHO- or FDA-selected strains
